    "bio": "I'm a developer with a strong foundation in networking and system administration, focused on building clean, efficient, and scalable web applications. I work mainly with React, Node.js, and real-time technologies like WebSockets, and I enjoy turning complex ideas into practical, user-friendly solutions. With CCNA- and MCSA-level knowledge, I bring a full-stack mindset that connects code, servers, and networks.",
    "story": "I'm a developer with a deep interest in how technology works from the ground up — from networks and servers to modern web applications. My journey started with networking and system administration, where I built a strong understanding of CCNA- and MCSA-level concepts like routing, switching, IP addressing, and system management. This foundation helped me see software not just as code, but as part of a larger, connected system.\n\nOver time, I moved into web development, focusing on building responsive and scalable applications using React, Node.js, and real-time technologies such as WebSockets. I enjoy creating systems that solve real-world problems, whether it's a live chat application, dashboards, or service-based platforms. I pay close attention to clean architecture, performance, and user experience.\n\nI'm a continuous learner who enjoys experimenting with new tools, improving existing systems, and understanding how backend logic, APIs, and infrastructure work together. My goal is to grow as a full-stack developer while building reliable, efficient, and impactful digital solutions.",
